Neolithic mural, Landscape with Volcano Eruption (Çatalhöyük, c. 6150 BCE). Lime plaster wall painting with red ochre, black, white. Flat, non-perspectival, geometric style; dense mud-brick houses, erupting double-coned volcano;,no shading, uses overlap/scale. Created for ritual and commemoration, honoring nature’s power, recording the landscape, and reinforcing communal identity in early settled life.
